			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				One of the things that all necros should know for PvP is how to use this line of spells.  Lifetap, Lifespike, etc is a MAJOR advantage in a duel.  Let's say you are challenged by EGODRUID to a duel.  Of course, knowing your class as you do, you first try to engulfing darkness and dot him.  Fear being the next line of attack.  Now some of this stuff will be resisted and Mr. EGODRUID being a druid will decide to use his nuke.  Now druid nukes are always going to be bigger than necro dd spells.  EGODRUID knows this and feels smug.  However, if you kindly wait until EGODRUID has nuked you to reply with a lifedrain spell of your own, you will have the mana advantage and beat him by attrition.  For while his spell does 30% more damage to you than your lifedrain spell, you GAIN 100% more life than he does with the SAME MANA.  If a necro can provoke a caster into a nuke war he/she can win.  It's simple numbers boys and girls.  EGODRUID has the same mana as you have, and you use your mana more efficiently.  So YOU can be the one feeling smug after your antagonist has opted to zone or has been anihilated by your arsenal.  Of course, if EGODRUID ever learns NOT to nuke you and instead decides to melee you, you are in trouble.  Then you will need your dots to try and win.  Also engulfing darkness can buy you time.  If the pet is rooted, lead EGODRUID past the rooted pet repeatedly, or stand in front of it so that your foe may recieve the brunt of your ally's anger.  <BR>
<BR>
Muertan
				</font>
			</td>

